<TextView android:layout_height="wrap_content" android:layout_width="wrap_content" android:id="@+id/textView33" android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall" android:text="Dedicated to Lord Shiva, this temple is located 37 km away from the main city. It lies on a river island in the River Mahanadi and serves as a popular weekend getaway for the people of Cuttack and other nearby towns. This temple, established back in 10th century AD is an important pilgrimage center and also provides a beautiful scenic and serene ambience. One can reach this place from Cuttack by using boats and ferries. There is also a foot-over bridge which people can use to reach this temple by paying a nominal fee." android:layout_alignLeft="@+id/imageView1" android:layout_alignBottom="@+id/imageView1"/>
